  "body": "### Description\n\nThe OIDC session-cookie from the extension `io.quarkus:quarkus-oidc` has the fixed name `q_session`.\r\n\r\n### Requirement:\r\nThe name of the cookie should be made configurable.\r\n\r\n### Problem\r\n* In our environment we have several applications running in a common domain across different stage-environments (development, testing, etc).\r\n* The applications need to share the cookie between separatly deployed UI and quarkus-services via domain-configuration by `quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-domain` settings.\r\n* Depending on the stage-environment different oidc providers might be used, so sharing of the cookie is not possible.\r\n* Separation by domain configuration is not possible in this case as all applications share the same domain in the different environments.\r\n\r\nIn combination this results in authentication errors when switching from an application in one stage-environment to another.\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
